               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>As part of the ongoing Cyber security programme, the University of Manchester wishes to enhance the capabilities of the current IT Security operations team and evolve it towards a Security Operations Centre (SOC) service.</P>
                  <P>The University wishes to deploy a hybrid operating model where the capabilities of the SOC are provided jointly between internal University staff and service providers.</P>
                  <P>The services provided by the SOC, and the operating model desired for each of them, have been defined by the University as the output of a current state assessment. The SOC is a part of the target operating model of both Information Governance Office (IGO) and transformed IT services.</P>
                  <P>A Security Operations Centre (SOC) is a central management facility that acts as a focal point for operational security management and platform monitoring, from an Information Security perspective, within an organisation. (It is also sometimes referred to as a Cyber SOC or CSOC).</P>
                  <P>The core business function of a SOC is to enable security incident reporting, detection, investigation, and response; using data from endpoint devices, logs, security systems, and network flows; in conjunction with clearly defined processes and specialist staff.</P>
                  <P>An effective SOC can build robust situational awareness and prioritize the deployment of enterprise resources to address security issues.</P>
                  <P>In addition to the core capabilities, a mature SOC also assists wider organisational security processes. These range from feeding into business risk assessment, compliance or internal audit through to technical control management and secure system architecture.</P>
                  <P>The SOC integrates with wider technology platform monitoring.</P>
                  <P>The University of Manchester wishes to improve the confidentiality, integrity, availability and authenticity of its systems and infrastructure by implementing a Security Operations Centre.</P>
                  <P>The Security Operation Centre will act as a central management facility to provide a continuous service to prevent, record, respond and manage cyber-security incidents.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
